ty that underlies effective protected area management. "\n        f"This is a broad proxy — actual PAME scores would require the GD-PAME database "\n        f"(requires account registration at BIOPAMA). "\n        f"Data quality caveat: WGI indicators cover all governance dimensions, not just PA management."\n    )\n\n    summary = (\n        f"Hypothesis SPI-H07 tests whether Protected Area Management Effectiveness (PAME) "\n        f"correlates with the Species Protection Index (SPI). Due to inaccessibility of the "\n        f"GD-PAME database, this analysis uses {proxy_label} (WGI) as an approximate proxy "\n        f"for institutional management quality. "\n        f"Bivariate correlation: Pearson r={corr.pearson_r:.3f} (p={corr.pearson_p:.4f}), "\n        f"Spearman rho={corr.spearman_rho:.3f} (p={corr.spearman_p:.4f}), "\n        f"N={corr.n_observations} observations across {corr.n_countries} countries. "\n        f"Best functional form: {form.best_form.value}. "\n        f"Verdict: {verdict.value}. Note: This is an exploratory test with a substitute proxy."\n    )\n\n    result = build_result_json(\n        HYPOTHESIS_ID,\n        verdict,\n        corr,\n        partial,\n        functional_form=form,\n        data_quality_notes=data_quality_notes,\n        summary=summary,\n    )\n    result["verification_method"] = "exploratory_test"\n    result["proxy_substitution"] = {\n        "intended_proxy": "Protected Area Management Effectiveness Score (PAME/METT-4)",\n        "actual_proxy": proxy_source,\n        "substitution_rationale": (\n            "Government Effectiveness (WGI) measures institutional quality, rule of law, "\n            "and governance capacity — the same institutional factors that determine whether "\n            "protected areas are managed effectively vs. remaining \'paper parks\'."\n        )\n    }\n\nelse:\n    # No proxy found — report inconclusive\n    print("\\n[RESULT] No usable proxy data found. Reporting inconclusive.")\n\n   