sm**: eDNA sampling generates direct measure of species presence, absence, and community composition change over time. Protected areas with high species diversity detected through eDNA sampling, combined with stable or improving detection, indicate effective species protection and should correlate strongly with SPI habitat representativeness measures.\n- **Confidence**: speculative\n- **Literature Evidence**: None\n\n## Data Source (may not be directly accessible)\n- **Name**: Conservation Genetics Labs eDNA programs\n- **Organization**: U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service, various research institutions\n- **URL**: https://www.fws.gov/project/environmental-dna-edna\n- **Format**: Database/research papers\n- **Accessibility**: restricted\n- **Coverage**: <5% countries with systematic programs, concentrated in North America, Australia, northern Europe\n\nThe hypothesis includes this URL — try fetching it first: https://www.fws.gov/project/environmental-dna-edna\n\n## References\n- https://www.fws.gov/project/environmental-dna-edna\n\n## EPI Target Data Summary\n**Target Indicator**: SPI — Species Protection Index\n**Units**: %\n**Polarity**: positive\n**Source**: MOL\n**Data File**: `/Users/samkouteili/rose/epi/multi-agent/docs/EPI2024_Work/Raw/SPI_raw.csv`\n**Coverage**: 178 countries, 1980-2024 (8010 observations)\n**Summary Stats**: mean=28.35, std=26.72, median=21.21\n\n**Control Variable Files**:\n- GPC: `/Users/samkouteili/rose/epi/multi-agent/docs/EPI2024_Work/Raw/GPC_raw.csv`\n- POP: `/Users/samkouteili/rose/epi/multi-agent/docs/EPI2024_Work/Raw/POP_raw.csv`\n- URB: `/Users/samkouteili/rose/epi/multi-agent/docs/EPI2024_Work/Raw/URB_raw.csv`\n\n## Caveats to Consider\n- Requires specialized laboratory equipment limiting accessibility\n- Minimal implementation in tropical developing regions where species diversity is highest\n- Temporal coverage typically 2-10 years per study location\n\n## Output Directory\nWrite ALL output files to: `/Users/samkouteili/rose/epi/mul